content.description: Start on a decent hold with low feet and do a big move to a crack on the right. Follow the crack to the top and top-out just above the crack.
content.protection: The landing on this boulder is fantastic. The ground is level and there isn't much to land on except for the crash-pad.
content.location: This route is on the same boulder as Cars and Trucks and Things That Go. The boulder is located near the left corner of the parking lot and is also about 200ft left of the bathrooms in the parking lot.

content.description: Start on blocky jugs on the right side of the boulder. Use the arete and other jugs as you climb up. Top it out and descend on your right.
content.protection: The landing is level, but beware of the tree a little to your left.
content.location: The boulder is located in the left corner of the Carderock parking lot.  It is near the climbs Turkey, Cars and Trucks and Things That Go, and The Parking Lot Traverse. The boulders are pretty obvious when you park.

content.description: Start near ground on the right side of the boulder on a good crimp and decent pinch. Work your way across the lip of the boulder until you are close to another block on your left. Top it out from there.
content.protection: The landing is completely level with nothing around.
content.location: This boulder is near the left corner of the Carderock parking lot. This boulder is just right of the boulder with the climbs Cars and Trucks and Things That Go, Turkey, and Road Rage. The boulder is also about 200ft left of the bathrooms in the Carderock parking lot.

climbs.name: Cars and Trucks and Things That Go

content.description: Start on decent hold under a large flake. Grab the large flake and use quartzite blobs and smalls crimps to bump to top. Top out using the blobs and crimps.
content.protection: The landing is great with level dirt and not much around to fall on except the crash-pad.
content.location: The boulder is near the left corner of the Carderock parking lot. Probably about 200ft left of the bathrooms in front of the parking lot.

content.description: A set of parking lot boulders (38.975885, -77.205251)
